.TH EIDOLON\-DRIFT 6 "2026-04-27" "0.9.5" "Games"
.SH NAME
eidolon\-drift \- terminal\-based incident response space horror game
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eidolon\-drift
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Eidolon Drift
is a curses\-based adventure game in which the player takes the role of an
incident responder aboard a distressed spaceship.
Navigate through the vessel, reach the Command Module, and escape via the
emergency pod while managing a deteriorating sanity level.
.PP
The game features procedural map generation, a sanity system that shrinks
the visible field of view, atmospheric ambient messages, and multiple colour
themes.
.SH CONTROLS
.SS Movement
.TP
.BR w / s / a / d
Move up, down, left, right.
.TP
Arrow keys
Alternative movement.
.TP
.B q
Quit the game.
.SS In\-game commands
Type a command at the prompt and press Enter.
.TP
.B scan
Run diagnostics on the current sector and list environmental readings
and detected objects.
.TP
.B logs
List readable log entries found in the current sector.
.TP
.BI inspect " <object>"
Read the details of an object or log in the current sector.
.TP
.BI decrypt " <object>"
Attempt to decrypt a fragmented data object.
.TP
.B map
Print a text snapshot of the ship layout.
.TP
.B status
Display current health, sanity level, and inventory.
.TP
.BI use " <object>"
Use an item from inventory or the current sector.
.TP
.BI theme " <name>"
Switch the colour theme.
Available themes:
.BR dark ", " retro ", " high_contrast .
.TP
.B help
Show the in\-game command reference.
.TP
.B quit
Exit the session.
.SH GAME MECHANICS
.SS Sanity
Sanity starts at 100 and decreases over time and in hazardous sectors.
As sanity falls the visible radius shrinks to a minimum of 20 % of its
original size.
Medbay sectors restore sanity.
.SS Objectives
.IP \(bu 4
Explore the ship and navigate to the Command Module.
.IP \(bu 4
Activate the emergency pod to complete the mission.
.IP \(bu 4
Avoid sanity loss from anomaly sectors.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/games/eidolon\-drift/
Game source and data files.
.TP
.I ~/crash.log
Crash report written to the working directory when an unhandled exception
occurs.
